snippet.textDisplay: I'm sitting here struggling not to tear up all over again and you might be right about God's plan in the end for him and Gigi. Kob accomplished so much in a short time and went out young but can you imagine the same for Gigi had she survived him? She most likely wouldn't touch a ball ever again. Like imagine that arrow within you that points to the game of basketball and life in general being broken beyond repair and the ONLY cobbler with the tools to attempt mending it cannot be found, what reason would you have for existence at 13 onward? She'd be messed up a long time and it would have been sad to witness so yeah...God's plan.
